{
  "stem": "2581.6",
  "chunk_idx": 7,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 10.4,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "Not all-- not everyone had the 25 grosze to go to the, you know, movie.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "But if we were good, behaved, you know, we got it.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "That was such a different kind of childhood than what you see today that it's very difficult for someone that wasn't around at that time to understand how it was.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "To give you an example, public school-- of course, there were mostly Jewish teachers.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "It was a Jewish public school.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But there were also the gentile teachers.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But the Jewish teachers-- there was one teacher, Franka Korn, that was like a mother.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "Now it wasn't just teachers.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "You had guardians, teachers, guardians.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "In other words, whatever you did in another class, they were still the guardian.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And shortly before the war-- I had to be 12 years, because when the war broke out I was 13.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "So that was at least one year before.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 13,
      "text": "We had what was called [NON-ENGLISH], which is a tea party.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 14,
      "text": "And she would put on a record player and teach us dancing.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "She was like a mother to us.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "I remember bringing the hot water from my house, because I lived very close.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And she taught me the tango, you know?",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "The same woman, the same woman, we were with her together in Germany after the war.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And being we had no parents, when we signed [NON-ENGLISH], engagement, with the rabbi, she was sitting next to me like-- between me and my wife-- like a mother, you know, and signed the document.",
      "word_count": 35
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And also she learned English herself.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And as soon as she took the English lessons, she brought in her children, whatever was left in Germany, maybe I don't know, four or five, and she taught us English.",
      "word_count": 31
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "She was a real important teacher, [INAUDIBLE] a wonderful person.",
      "word_count": 10
    }
  ],
